      <h1 class='title'>Powers to vary, discharge, suspend or revive order</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c284GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_284gc' title='Col. 284GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c284GC' name='column_284gc' href='#column_284gc' rel='bookmark'>284GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03720'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_331' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        38 (1) If the court has made an order to which this Part applies, it may&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) vary or discharge the order,</li>
        <li>(b) suspend any provision of it temporarily, or</li>
        <li>(c) revive the operation of any provision so suspended.</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03721'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_332' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) Sub-paragraph (1) is subject to the provisions of this Part and paragraph 34(5).
      </p>
